## 4. Porting Checklist

### Install dependencies

```bash
npm install framer-motion clsx tailwind-merge
```

### Files to copy

- [ ] [StatsSection.tsx](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/components/home/StatsSection.tsx) → your components directory
- [ ] [Container.tsx](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/components/ui/Container.tsx) → your UI components directory (or replace `<Container>` with your own max-width wrapper)
- [ ] [utils.ts](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/lib/utils.ts) → your lib directory (or replace [cn()](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/lib/utils.ts#4-7) with `clsx` directly if you don't use `tailwind-merge`)

### Theme tokens to add

Add to your CSS / Tailwind config:

| Token | Value | Used for |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-primary-400` | `#829ab1` | Label text color (`text-primary-400`) |
| `--font-display` | `Arial, sans-serif` | Number font family (`font-display`) |

Or replace these Tailwind classes with your own equivalents:
- `text-primary-400` → any muted grey for labels
- `font-display` → any display/heading font family

### Customizing

| What | Where to change |
|---|---|
| **Stat values** | `value` prop on each `<StatItem>` |
| **Labels** | `label` prop  |
| **Number colors** | `colorClass` prop (Tailwind arbitrary: `text-[#HEX]`) |
| **Suffix** | `suffix` prop (defaults to `"+"`) |
| **Count-up duration** | Second arg to [useCountUp()](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/components/home/StatsSection.tsx#7-37) (default `2000` ms) |
| **Trigger offset** | `margin` in `useInView` options (default `"-100px"`) |
| **Easing** | Currently linear; add an easing function to the `progress` calculation in [useCountUp](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/components/home/StatsSection.tsx#7-37) |
| **Section background** | `bg-white` on the `<section>` |
| **Section padding** | `py-20` on the `<section>` |

### Where to place in your Home page

```tsx
import { StatsSection } from "@/components/home/StatsSection";

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <>
      {/* … sections above … */}
      <StatsSection />
      {/* … sections below … */}
    </>
  );
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> [StatsSection.tsx](file:///Users/zhengpeixian/ZPX/Work/KEA/KE_Academy/ke-academy-next/src/components/home/StatsSection.tsx) uses `"use client"` because it relies on `useState`, `useEffect`, and `useInView` — all client-side APIs. Make sure your target project supports React client components.
